I thought today would be the perfect day to introduce myself.  I’m Jade, the owner of Wax Appeal Hawaii for the last 16 years and I’ve been an esthetician for 21 years!  I am absolutely thrilled to still be of service for all the amazing people who walk through my door!  I’m beyond grateful for all of the support and have trust in me. 
I’ve started this Instagram page about a year ago and have found so much inspiration from all the amazing esthies on IG that has sparked my passion for making waxing videos for you!
A little about me when I’m not in the wax room:
The truth is I’m chatty and social with my clients, but I’m an introvert otherwise.  I hate social events because I feel super awkward.  I like to watch an observe and I actually learn this way too! 
I love being crafty and artistic and paint whenever I have the time.
I love new adventures, travel, and the outdoors like hiking and mountain biking. 
About 10 years ago I learned how to ride a street motorcycle and soon took up a hobby in dirt biking. I worked very hard and was deeply determined to be able to ride with all the boys. I’ve also competed and won hard enduro races among girls that were less then half my age! 
At this point in my life, I’ve proven to myself that with hard work and determination, I can do anything at almost any age!  I hope to inspire you too, to just do it!! Life is too short to make excuses!!! 
Live life to its fullest!
Professional photography done by the amazing artist: @tracywrightcorvo @soullightportraits thanks for making me feel comfortable in front of the camera! (For those who know me know I hate taking pictures!!!)

#soloesthetician #waxingspecialist #hawaiiwaxing #waxinghawaii #hawaiismallbusiness #smallbusinessowner

Bikini Waxing✨ this is for mature audiences who understand that hair is a natural part of our bodies.  I have always felt embarrassed about having excess hair in my bikini area and waxing helped me get over being self conscious about it.  Waxing is part of self-care and not just for the summer time.  Consistently waxing every 4-6 weeks will result in less pain and finer hair growth.

Pro Tip: room temperature should be set at about 73-75 degrees F and is great for humid environments.

Leg Waxing Video✨
Let’s talk about temperature.  There’s so many variables that make your wax work best. 
The temperature of the wax is number one!  You don’t want to burn the skin so of course setting it to the perfect temp makes things great! 
But that’s not all.  With Nova’s quick drying formula, your room temperature is about just as important when doing a leg wax (IMO)! If you’re setting the room temperature anywhere in the 60’s, it’s probably going to cause your wax strip to break or crack.  The best temperature for a leg wax would be about 70-72 degrees F. 
Body temperature, humidity level, and the outside temperature all matter. 
Learning a new wax takes time and effort so you want to buy 2 pounds MINIMUM to practice and play with it. 
Purchase @nova_wax and use code “JADE” for an additional 20% off!  Offer lasts until September 30th!!

Lash lift BTS ✨ 
Ever wonder what goes on during a lash lift? Here’s a quick clip of removing the solution from the shields. 
Pro Tips:
-Use a small slant tip brush to remove the product. The slant tip brush makes it easier to get into every nook and cranny better than just a Q-tip.  Then go over the lashes with a wet Q-tip to ensure that all the product is removed.

Lash lift lasts up to 8 weeks.

Knee waxing tips!
Knee waxing can be a little tricky!  The skin is usually very thick and dry.
Tips:
-Bend the knee before applying wax so it stretches the skin tight.
-Use a thick layer of wax to ensure that the wax doesn’t break.
-Remove the wax with a staggered pull. This helps get the wax off over the curved area.

How do you prepare the skin for a wax?
If I’m using hard wax, I always use powder!  This video shows exactly why!  The wax works really well, but all wax soft or hard, will not mix with moisture. 
Wax cannot work properly if moisture is present no matter how good the wax is.  This is why being able to have a quick dry formula like @nova_wax is so important! 
The longer the wax sits on the skin, the more it becomes sweaty. 
Try this to experiment on yourself: apply a large strip on your leg or arm and let it sit for a whole minute or two.  Remove the wax and I assure you that it will have moisture there from sitting so long!
